      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "A large oil painting on canvas (93 x 137 cm) by **Jacobus van Looy** (Haarlem, 1855 – Haarlem, 1930), depicting a lush garden in full summer bloom. A woman in a hat kneels among nasturtiums, California poppies, and sunflowers. Painted in the summer of **1893** en plein air in the backyard of Van Looy's house on Rustenburgerstraat in Amsterdam's De Pijp neighbourhood, with his wife **Titia van Gelder** as the figure in the garden. Acquired in November 2013 and immediately designated one of Teylers' **50 Topstukken**.",
